艾玛·汤普森的朋友，曾与她在《[[亨利五世_(1989年电影)|亨利五世]]》（{{lang|en|''Henry V''}}）、《[[无事生非_(电影)|无事生非]]》和《再续前世情》中合作过的[[作曲家|作曲家]][[帕特里克·道尔|帕特里克·道尔]]获聘为《理智与情感》谱写音乐<ref name="chicagotimessense" />。导演要求他从已有的音乐作品中加以挑选，或是创作新的“温柔”旋律，多尔于是根据电影的情节谱写了一段曲目<ref name="Parrill" />{{rp|43}}<ref name="RockyMtNews">{{cite news |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-67774405.html |title=Score one for the movies: composers translate plot, character and setting into Oscar-nominated music |work=Rocky Mountain News |via=HighBeam Research |first=John |last=Horn |date=1996-03-13 |accessdate=2014-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140611025851/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-67774405.html |archive-date=2014-06-11 |dead-url=yes }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。他表示，在这种英国中产阶级的音乐主题下，必须时而出现一次感情上的爆发<ref name="chicagotimessense">{{cite news |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1996-03-01/entertainment/9603010027_1_sense-and-sensibility-classical-music-patrick-doyle |title=Composer's classical music makes 'Sense' in movies |first=Brad |last=Webber |work=Chicago Tribune |date=1996-03-01 |accessdate=2014-01-29 ||archivedate=2012-10-06 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20121006054839/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1996-03-01/entertainment/9603010027_1_sense-and-sensibility-classical-music-patrick-doyle}}</ref>。道尔还称，随着剧情推进到一个更成熟，并带有情感上宣泻的意味时，相应的配乐也变得更加成熟<ref name="RockyMtNews" />。影片的音乐中包含浪漫元素<ref name="allmusic">{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/sense-and-sensibility-mw0000646538 |title=Sense and Sensibility – Patrick Doyle |work=Allmusic |first=Darryl |last=Carter |accessdate=2014-01-29 |archivedate=2013-06-13 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130624014459/http://www.allmusic.com/album/sense-and-sensibility-mw0000646538}}</ref><ref name="DenofGeekMusic">{{cite news |url=http://www.denofgeek.us/movies/17369/music-in-the-movies-patrick-doyle |title=Music in the movies: Patrick Doyle |publisher=Den of Geek |first=Glen |last=Chapman |date=2011-04-21 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140129030727/http://www.denofgeek.us/movies/17369/music-in-the-movies-patrick-doyle |accessdate=2014-01-29 |deadurl=no |archivedate=2014-01-29}}</ref>，[[全国公共广播电台|全国公共广播电台]]形容乐曲为“感情……受限的指南针”，“乐器以轻柔的方式排列交融在一起”<ref name="NPRmusic">{{cite news |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-28473770.html |via=HighBeam Research |title=Film scores – The men who make the music – Part 2 |publisher=National Public Radio |first=Liane |last=Hansen |date=1996-03-10 |accessdate=2013-04-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140611025948/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-28473770.html |archive-date=2014-06-11 |dead-url=yes }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。评论中还指出，作为对故事情节的一种反射，这些配乐“有些怅惘……和感伤”<ref name="NPRmusic" />。

片中玛丽安演唱了两首[[歌曲|歌曲]]，歌词均改编自17世纪的诗作。李安觉得这两首歌曲传达出小说和剧本中的“双重愿景”<ref name="Parrill" />{{rp|43}}。他认为第二首歌表现了玛丽安“成熟的接纳”与“忧郁的理智”相交织的情感<ref name="Parrill" />{{rp|43}}。玛丽安所唱第一首歌“{{lang|en|Weep You No More Sad Fountains}}”的旋律于电影开场字幕时首次出现，而第二首歌的旋律则在片尾字幕时再度响起，并改由戏剧[[女高音|女高音]][[简·依格伦|简·依格伦]]（{{lang|en|Jane Eaglen}}）演唱<ref name="Parrill" />{{rp|43}}。这两首歌都是影片开拍前由道尔创作的<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-8896491.html |via=HighBeam Research |title=Classical composer aims to score for charity |work=The Independent |first=Charlotte |last=Cripps |date=2007-10-15 |accessdate=14 April 2013 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130629103713/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-8896491.html |archive-date=2013-06-29 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，他也因本片的配乐而首次得到[[奥斯卡最佳原创配乐奖|奥斯卡最佳原创配乐奖]]提名<ref name="DenofGeekMusic" />。
