《理智与情感》获得了影评人压倒性的好评。根据[[烂蕃茄|烂蕃茄]]上收集的52篇专业评论文章，其中有51篇给出了“新鲜”的正面评价，“新鲜度”98%，平均得分7.9（最高10分）<ref name="tomatoes">{{cite web |archivedate=2013-10-24 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131024160823/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1068832-sense_and_sensibility/ |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1068832-sense_and_sensibility/ | title=Sense and Sensibility (1995) | publisher=Flixster | work=Rotten Tomatoes | accessdate=2014-01-29}}</ref>；而在{{lang|en|[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]}}上收集的21篇评论文章则全部给出好评，综合评分84（最高100）<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/sense-and-sensibility |title=Sense and Sensibility |publisher=CBS |work=Metacritic |accessdate=2014-01-29 |archivedate=2012-04-19 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120419045119/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/sense-and-sensibility}}</ref>。影片还登上了超过100个影评人或媒体评选的年度十大佳片榜单<ref name="tcmfmiller" />。《[[综艺|综艺]]》杂志的托德·麦卡锡（{{lang|en|Todd McCarthy}}）认为，影片的成功与“众演员的纯熟演技”，以及选择李安作为导演的决定密不可分。他在评论中指出，虽然李安之前在社会和世代性传统的戏剧化冲突方面表现出的才能不容质疑，但他在本片中的表现已经远远超出了任何人的预期，而且很可能可以与[[石黑一雄|石黑一雄]]写作《[[长日将尽|长日将尽]]》相提并论。<ref>{{cite news |first= Todd |last= McCarthy |archivedate=2013-11-11 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131111085331/http://variety.com/1995/film/reviews/sense-and-sensibility-3-1200444193/ |url= http://variety.com/1995/film/reviews/sense-and-sensibility-3-1200444193/ |title= Sense and Sensibility |work=Variety |date= 1995-12-03 |accessdate= 2014-01-29}}</ref>

《[[旧金山纪事报|旧金山纪事报]]》的米克·拉萨尔（{{lang|en|Mick LaSalle}}）称赞了影片中的紧迫感，“让一个不起眼的18世纪家庭面临的问题显得既直接又私人”<ref name="sfgate">{{cite news |archivedate=2013-11-04 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131104095404/http://www.sfgate.com/movies/article/A-Fine-Sensibility-Emma-Thompson-adapts-Jane-3018044.php |url= http://www.sfgate.com/movies/article/A-Fine-Sensibility-Emma-Thompson-adapts-Jane-3018044.php |title= A fine 'Sensibility', Emma Thompson adapts Jane Austen's classic story |work= San Francisco Chronicle |date= 1995-12-13 |first= Mick |last= LaSalle |accessdate= 2014-01-29}}</ref>。拉萨尔总结认为，这部改编作品在“讽刺和温馨中找到了恰当的平衡”，影片在理解和情感上都非常清晰，镜头中带着一种从未被要求过需要做到的优雅<ref name="sfgate" />。影评人约翰·西蒙（{{lang|en|John Simon}}）对本片推崇倍至，并特别注重于汤普森的表演，不过他批评了格兰特的表现有些“太装可爱……他在银幕上的人物形象急需管教，别再老像头[[单峰骆驼|单峰骆驼]]那样拱起肩膀了”<ref name=Simon-2005>{{cite book |first=John Ivan |last=Simon |title=John Simon On Film: Criticism, 1982–2001|url=https://archive.org/details/johnsimononfilmc0000simo |publisher=Applause Books |year=2005 |isbn=978-1-55783-507-9 |page=[https://archive.org/details/johnsimononfilmc0000simo/page/484 484]}}</ref>。

《[[周日邮报|周日邮报]]》的威廉·利思（{{lang|en|William Leith}}）称赞《理智与情感》是“一部极其尖锐、含蓄、巧妙、迷人的电影”，比电视短剧《傲慢与偏见》更加优秀。他还特别表扬了演员们的表现，称格兰特“纯熟”地扮演了自己的角色，哈丽特·瓦尔特也成功传达出了那种出人意料的尖酸刻薄<ref>{{cite news |first=William |last=Leith |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-110854966.html |title=Needle work |work=The Mail on Sunday |via=HighBeam Research |date=1996-02-25 |accessdate=2014-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111044908/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-110854966.html |archive-date=2013-11-11 |dead-url=yes }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。加尔·卡尔（{{lang|en|Jarr Carr}}）在《[[波士顿环球报|波士顿环球报]]》（{{lang|en|''The Boston Globe''}}）上发表的文章中称，李安“精确地把握住了奥斯汀尖锐的社会观察和浓郁的讽刺意味”，他还认为汤普森和温丝莱特在年龄方面与原著人物的出入是表现理智与情感分别的一个积极因素<ref>{{cite news |first=Jay |last=Carr |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-8355832.html |title=Thompson makes glorious 'Sense' |via=HighBeam Research |work=The Boston Globe |date=1995-12-13 |accessdate=2014-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111044859/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-8355832.html |archive-date=2013-11-11 |dead-url=yes }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。《[[广播时报|广播时报]]》的大卫·帕金森（{{lang|en|David Parkinson}}）也同样欣赏李安的导演能力，称赞他避免了把许多英国古装片变得低俗的巧克力盒式视觉效果，“给这个两姐妹的故事带来令人耳目一新的真实感，让艾玛·汤普森赢得奥斯卡奖肯定的剧本得到充分的发挥”<ref name="RadioTimesreview" />。

